  "prompt": "When will Intel start hiring new candidates following the 2016 layoffs?",
  "response": "Intel did conduct layoffs in 2016 as part of a broader restructuring effort to shift its focus from PCs to more growth-oriented areas like cloud computing and IoT (Internet of Things). The layoffs affected about 12,000 employees worldwide. However, Intel continued to hire new candidates even during and after the layoffs, particularly in strategic areas where the company wanted to grow.\n\nThe exact timing of when Intel started hiring again broadly likely varied by location and department, but the company did not completely halt hiring during or after the layoffs. Intel has historically balanced layoffs in certain divisions with hiring in others to align with its strategic priorities.\n\nIf you're looking for specific information about Intel's hiring practices post-2016, it would be best to monitor Intel's career page or reach out to their HR department for the most accurate and up-to-date information. The company's hiring needs are influenced by market conditions, business priorities, and technological advancements, so opportunities can arise at any time.",
